SlbAdminState.name: SlbAdminState
SlbAdminState.description: The administrative state of various SLB entities 'disable' : The entity has been disabled. 'enable' : The entity is enabled so it can participate in the load balancing activity.

SlbOperState.name: SlbOperState
SlbOperState.description: The operational state of various SLB entities 'outOfService' : The entity is out of service. 'inService' : The entity operates properly.

SlbRedirectAlgorithm.name: SlbRedirectAlgorithm
SlbRedirectAlgorithm.description: The load-balancing algorithm being used on a cluster to distribute load evenly among real servers. 'roundRobin' load-balancing delivers connections evenly amongst real servers while 'serverFailover' gives new connections to the real server only when the previous has failed.

SlbHashSelector.name: SlbHashSelector
SlbHashSelector.description: The hashing algorithm to use when distributing the packets across the server.

SlbServerOperState.name: SlbServerOperState
SlbServerOperState.description: The server operational state represents the state of a real server being load-balanced by SLB. 'inService' : Server is in use as a destination for SLB client connections. 'linkDown' : The link by which the server can be reached has failed, so the server is considered out of service. 'noAnswer' : The server has not answered to a sequence of ping retries, so the server is considered out of service. 'disabled' : Server has been disabled by the admin status, so the server is considered out of service. 'retrying' : The server is currently being tested for a number of retries. It is still considered in service. 'discovery' : The server is currently being tested to get its MAC address. The server is considered out of service.

slbAdminStatus.name: slbAdminStatus
slbAdminStatus.description: The administrative status of the SLB feature. It allows to turn on/off the feature

slbOperStatus.name: slbOperStatus
slbOperStatus.description: The operational status of the SLB feature. 'inService' means that at least one cluster of servers is inService. 'outOfService' means that all of defined clusters of servers are outOfService.

slbClusterTable.name: slbClusterTable
slbClusterTable.description: This is a table of clusters, each of which is a group of real servers to be used by SLB for load balancing. Columnar objects can be modified when the row is 'active'. Rows can be created and destroyed. Entries are added to this table via slbClusterRowStatus in accordance with the RowStatus convention.

slbClusterAdminStatus.name: slbClusterAdminStatus
slbClusterAdminStatus.description: The administrative state of the cluster.

slbClusterOperStatus.name: slbClusterOperStatus
slbClusterOperStatus.description: The operational state of the cluster.

slbClusterVIP.name: slbClusterVIP
slbClusterVIP.description: The Virtual IP address for that cluster.

slbClusterPingPeriod.name: slbClusterPingPeriod
slbClusterPingPeriod.description: The ping period to check health of servers.

slbClusterPingTimeout.name: slbClusterPingTimeout
slbClusterPingTimeout.description: The timeout used to wait for ping answers.

slbClusterPingRetries.name: slbClusterPingRetries
slbClusterPingRetries.description: The number of ping retries before deciding that a server is OutOfService.

slbClusterRedirectAlgorithm.name: slbClusterRedirectAlgorithm
slbClusterRedirectAlgorithm.description: The load balancing algorithm in use by the cluster.

slbClusterIdleTimer.name: slbClusterIdleTimer
slbClusterIdleTimer.description: The maximum delay with no activity a client is kept attached to a real server.

slbClusterNumberOfServers.name: slbClusterNumberOfServers
slbClusterNumberOfServers.description: The number of real servers in this cluster.

slbClusterNewFlows.name: slbClusterNewFlows
slbClusterNewFlows.description: The number of flows balanced for this cluster.

slbClusterRowStatus.name: slbClusterRowStatus
slbClusterRowStatus.description: The object is used by a management station to create or delete the row entry in slbClusterTable following the RowStatus textual convention.

slbClusterProbeName.name: slbClusterProbeName
slbClusterProbeName.description: The name of the cluster's probe.

slbClusterPackets.name: slbClusterPackets
slbClusterPackets.description: The number of packets passed for this cluster.

slbClusterCondition.name: slbClusterCondition
slbClusterCondition.description: The Condition name rule. Mutually exclusive with VIP

slbClusterType.name: slbClusterType
slbClusterType.description: The type of load balancing. l3 - routed, l2flows - distribute bridged flows

slbClusterHashType.name: slbClusterHashType
slbClusterHashType.description: The load balancing hashing algorithm by the cluster.

slbServerTable.name: slbServerTable
slbServerTable.description: A table of real servers. Columnar objects can be modified when the row is 'active'. Rows can be created and destroyed. Entries are added to this table via slbServerRowStatus in accordance with the RowStatus convention.

slbServerTableEntry.name: slbServerTableEntry
slbServerTableEntry.description: Information about a particular real server in a particular cluster.

slbServerIpAddress.name: slbServerIpAddress
slbServerIpAddress.description: The IP address of real server.

slbServerAdminStatus.name: slbServerAdminStatus
slbServerAdminStatus.description: The administrative status of the server.

slbServerOperStatus.name: slbServerOperStatus
slbServerOperStatus.description: The operational status of the server.

slbServerAdminWeight.name: slbServerAdminWeight
slbServerAdminWeight.description: The Administrative weight of the real server used by the load-balancing algorithms. A weight of zero indicates that no new connections will be assigned to this real server. Higher weight values indicate to the load-balancing algorithms a higher availability of this real server to accept more work.

slbServerLastRTT.name: slbServerLastRTT
slbServerLastRTT.description: The last valid round trip time measured by ping.

slbServerPingFails.name: slbServerPingFails
slbServerPingFails.description: The number of pings that have failed on this server.

slbServerPortDown.name: slbServerPortDown
slbServerPortDown.description: The number of down events received at server port.

slbServerFlows.name: slbServerFlows
slbServerFlows.description: The number of flows directed to this server.

slbServerRowStatus.name: slbServerRowStatus
slbServerRowStatus.description: The object used by a management station to create or delete the row entry in slbServerTable following the RowStatus textual convention.

slbServerProbeStatus.name: slbServerProbeStatus
slbServerProbeStatus.description: The status from doing a probe.

slbProbeTable.name: slbProbeTable
slbProbeTable.description: This is a table of probes, each of which can be used in either the server or cluster tables to define the method that the will be used to determine the status of servers. Columnar objects can be modified when the row is 'active'. Rows can be created and destroyed. Entries are added to this table via slbProbeRowStatus in accordance with the RowStatus convention.

slbProbeMethod.name: slbProbeMethod
slbProbeMethod.description: The probe method used to check the health of servers.

slbProbePeriod.name: slbProbePeriod
slbProbePeriod.description: The probe period to check health of servers.

slbProbeTimeout.name: slbProbeTimeout
slbProbeTimeout.description: The timeout used to wait for probe answers.

slbProbeRetries.name: slbProbeRetries
slbProbeRetries.description: The number of probe retries before deciding that a server is OutOfService.

slbProbePort.name: slbProbePort
slbProbePort.description: The TCP/UDP port the probe should be sent on.

slbProbeExpect.name: slbProbeExpect
slbProbeExpect.description: An ASCII string used to compare a response from a server to verify the health of the server.

slbProbeSSL.name: slbProbeSSL
slbProbeSSL.description: Indicates if a TCP/UDP probe uses SSL.

slbProbeSend.name: slbProbeSend
slbProbeSend.description: An ASCII string sent to a server to invoke a response from a server to verify the health of the server.

slbProbeHttpStatus.name: slbProbeHttpStatus
slbProbeHttpStatus.description: The expected status returned from an HTTP GET to verify the health of the server.

slbProbeHttpUrl.name: slbProbeHttpUrl
slbProbeHttpUrl.description: A URL sent to a server for an HTTP GET to verify the health of the server.

slbProbeHttpUsername.name: slbProbeHttpUsername
slbProbeHttpUsername.description: An ASCII string sent to a server as credentials for an HTTP GET to verify the health of the server.

slbProbeHttpPassword.name: slbProbeHttpPassword
slbProbeHttpPassword.description: An ASCII string sent to a server as credentials for an HTTP GET to verify the health of the server. This string will be encrypted so it will not display readable.

slbProbeRowStatus.name: slbProbeRowStatus
slbProbeRowStatus.description: The object is used by a management station to create or delete the row entry in slbProbeTable following the RowStatus textual convention.
